{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777014456166,"sessionID":"ses_241d9f7b3ffeMqi0Lc2w61CcA3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"background_output","callID":"call_QlstEFdI3vfx8X9aCgOC18lv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"block":false,"full_session":false,"include_thinking":false,"include_tool_results":false,"message_limit":20,"since_message_id":"","task_id":"bg_8549826c","thinking_max_chars":2000,"timeout":60000},"output":"Task Result\n\nTask ID: bg_8549826c\nDescription: Research project registries\nDuration: 1m 54s\nSession ID: ses_241b23c79ffeRMl70ekzvJT6yI\n\n---\n\nThis is a comprehensive research request about file-based project structures and queryable project registries. Let me classify this request first.\n\n**TYPE D: COMPREHENSIVE RESEARCH** - This is a complex, ambiguous request that requires deep dive into multiple systems.\n\nThe user wants me to research:\n1. Remote/open-source and official documentation patterns\n2. File-based project structures\n3. Queryable project registries\n\nExamples to cover:\n- Cargo workspaces\n- Nx project.json\n- pyproject.toml\n- GitHub Projects fields\n- Backstage catalog-info.yaml\n- Kubernetes labels/selectors\n- Task/backlog systems\n- ADR indexes\n\nFocus areas:\n- Metadata schema\n- Registry/index design\n- Query modes (by name/status/lifecycle/type/tags/owner/updated time)\n\nGoal: Design recommendations for an AI agent project-manager\n\nThis requires Documentation Discovery (Phase 0.5) since it's about understanding patterns from multiple libraries/frameworks. However, many of these are not \"libraries\" in the traditional sense - they're formats/standards.\n\nLet me approach this systematically:\n\n1. First, I should search for official documentation for each of these systems\n2. Then research their metadata schemas and query capabilities\n3. Synthesize findings into design recommendations\n\nLet me start with finding official documentation for the key systems mentioned.\n\n\n## Phase 0: Request Classification\n\n**TYPE D: COMPREHENSIVE RESEARCH** — Complex multi-system research requiring documentation discovery across Cargo workspaces, Nx, pyproject.toml, GitHub Projects, Backstage, Kubernetes labels, and task systems.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 0.5: Documentation Discovery\n\nLet me find official documentation for each system to understand their project structure and registry patterns.\n\n\nNow let me search for Kubernetes labels/selectors and ADR (Architecture Decision Records) patterns, as well as task/backlog systems.\n\n\nNow let me get the official documentation for the Cargo workspaces and Backstage by fetching the actual documentation pages to get more concrete examples.\n\n\nNow let me fetch the official documentation for concrete examples and schema details:\n\n\nNow I have comprehensive information from official documentation. Let me synthesize all of this into a thorough research report with design recommendations for an AI agent project-manager.\n\nLet me compile the key patterns:\n\n1. **Cargo Workspaces**\n   - Metadata schema: workspace.metadata table (free-form), workspace.package for inheritance\n   - Registry: members/exclude lists in root Cargo.toml\n   - Query modes: path-based (members list), name-based (package names)\n\n2. **Nx project.json**\n   - Metadata schema: tags, implicitDependencies, namedInputs, targets\n   - Registry: nx.json workspace config + project.json files\n   - Query modes: by tags, projectType, implicitDependencies\n\n3. **pyproject.toml**\n   - Metadata schema: [project] table (name, version, description, dependencies, etc.), [tool.*] for tool-specific\n   - Registry: Each project has its own pyproject.toml\n   - Query modes: by name, dynamic/static fields\n\n4. **GitHub Projects**\n   - Metadata schema: custom fields (text, single-select, date, iteration, etc.)\n   - Registry: Organization/user projects\n   - Query modes: GraphQL/REST API with filtering\n\n5. **Backstage catalog-info.yaml**\n   - Metadata schema: apiVersion, kind, metadata (name, namespace, labels, annotations, tags, links), spec\n   - Registry: Software catalog with entity kinds (Component, API, Template, etc.)\n   - Query modes: by kind, owner, lifecycle, type, tags, system\n\n6. **Kubernetes labels/selectors**\n   - Metadata schema: key/value labels, matchLabels, matchExpressions\n   - Registry: etcd\n   - Query modes: equality-based (=, ==, !=), set-based (in, notin, exists, DoesNotExist)\n\n7. **ADR indexes**\n   - Metadata schema: status, context, decision, consequences, alternatives\n   - Registry: doc/adr/ directory with numbered markdown files\n   - Query modes: by number, status, date\n\n8. **Task/backlog systems**\n   - Metadata schema: status, priority, tags, assignees, depends_on, created/modified timestamps\n   - Registry: Various (TaskRepo, TICK.md, backlog.md, TaskBadger)\n   - Query modes: by status, priority, assignee, tags, due date\n\nI need to pull together concrete examples and formulate specific guidance for implementing an AI agent project-manager that can work with these diverse systems.\n\n\nNow let me compile the comprehensive research into a structured report with design recommendations.\n\n---\n\n# Research: File-Based Project Structures & Queryable Registries\n\n## 1. System-by-System Analysis\n\n### 1.1 Cargo Workspaces\n\n**Documentation**: [The Cargo Book - Workspaces](https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/reference/workspaces.html)\n\n**Metadata Schema**:\n```toml\n[workspace]\nmembers = [\"crate1\", \"crate2\"]\nexclude = [\"crates/foo\"]\ndefault-members = [\"crate1\"]\n\n[workspace.package]        # Inheritable keys\nversion = \"1.0.0\"\nauthors = [\"Team\"]\n\n[workspace.dependencies]   # Shared dependencies\nserde = \"1.0\"\n\n[workspace.metadata]        # Free-form for external tools\nwebcontents.root = \"web/\"\n```\n\n**Registry Design**:\n- Centralized: Root `Cargo.toml` defines workspace membership\n- Discovery: Globs (`crates/*`) + explicit `members` list\n- Inheritance model: `workspace.package` keys inherited via `{key}.workspace = true`\n\n**Query Modes**:\n| Mode | Mechanism |\n|------|-----------|\n| By name | Package `name` field in `Cargo.toml` |\n| By path | `members` list / directory structure |\n| By lifecycle | None native (external tools use `workspace.metadata`) |\n| By tags | None native |\n| By owner | None native |\n| By updated time | `cargo metadata` returns resolve order |\n\n**Key Insight**: Cargo intentionally leaves `workspace.metadata` unstructured for external tooling — a deliberate extension point.\n\n---\n\n### 1.2 Nx project.json\n\n**Documentation**: [Nx Project Configuration](https://nx.dev/docs/reference/project-configuration)\n\n**Metadata Schema**:\n```json\n{\n  \"root\": \"libs/mylib/\",\n  \"sourceRoot\": \"libs/mylib/src\",\n  \"projectType\": \"library\",\n  \"tags\": [\"scope:myteam\", \"type:ui\"],\n  \"implicitDependencies\": [\"@org/shared-utils\"],\n  \"namedInputs\": {\n    \"default\": [\"{projectRoot}/**/*\"],\n    \"production\": [\"!{projectRoot}/**/*.spec.tsx\"]\n  },\n  \"targets\": {\n    \"build\": { \"executor\": \"@nx/angular:build\", \"outputs\": [\"{workspaceRoot}/dist/...\"] },\n    \"test\": { \"dependsOn\": [\"build\"], \"executor\": \"@nx/jest:jest\" }\n  },\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"description\": \"Shared UI components\",\n    \"responsible\": \"platform-team\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Registry Design**:\n- Distributed: Each project has `project.json` (or `package.json` with `nx` property)\n- Central: `nx.json` defines `targetDefaults`, `namedInputs`, `plugins`\n- Discovery: Project inference from `project.json` files + plugins\n\n**Query Modes**:\n| Mode | Mechanism |\n|------|-----------|\n| By name | `projects` key in `workspace.json` or filename |\n| By status | `implicitDependencies` for dependency graph |\n| By lifecycle | `projectType` (library/application) |\n| By tags | `tags` array — enforced by `implicitDependencies` rules |\n| By owner | `metadata.responsible` (custom) |\n| By updated time | File system / git |\n\n**Key Insight**: Nx's tag system enforces module boundaries — tags like `scope:frontend` can block cross-scope imports.\n\n---\n\n### 1.3 pyproject.toml (PEP 621)\n\n**Documentation**: [pyproject.toml Specification](https://packaging.python.org/specifications/pyproject-toml/)\n\n**Metadata Schema**:\n```toml\n[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=61.0\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\nname = \"mypackage\"\nversion = \"1.0.0\"\ndescription = \"A short description\"\nreadme = \"README.md\"\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\nlicense = {text = \"MIT\"}\nauthors = [{name = \"Team\", email = \"team@example.com\"}]\nkeywords = [\"foo\", \"bar\"]\nclassifiers = [\"Programming Language :: Python :: 3\"]\ndependencies = [\"requests>=2.28\"]\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\ndev = [\"pytest\", \"ruff\"]\nllm = [\"openai\"]\n\n[project.urls]\nHomepage = \"https://example.com\"\nRepository = \"https://github.com/example/mypackage\"\n\n[tool.ruff]\nline-length = 88\n\n[tool.pytest.ini_options]\ntestpaths = [\"tests\"]\n```\n\n**Registry Design**:\n- Distributed: One `pyproject.toml` per Python package\n- Standardized `[project]` table (PEP 621) for metadata\n- `[tool.*]` namespace for tool-specific config (unregulated)\n\n**Query Modes**:\n| Mode | Mechanism |\n|------|-----------|\n| By name | `project.name` |\n| By version | `project.version` (static or `dynamic`) |\n| By dependencies | `project.dependencies` |\n| By tags | `project.keywords` / `project.classifiers` |\n| By owner | `project.authors` |\n| By updated time | External (PyPI, git) |\n\n**Key Insight**: PEP 621 enforces that only `[project]` table fields defined in the spec may be added — tools must use `[tool.*]` for custom fields.\n\n---\n\n### 1.4 GitHub Projects (V2)\n\n**Documentation**: [REST API for Projects](https://docs.github.com/en/rest/projects/projects), [Fields API](https://docs.github.com/en/rest/projects/fields)\n\n**Metadata Schema** (via GraphQL):\n```graphql\ntype ProjectV2 {\n  id: ID!\n  number: Int!\n  title: String!\n  items(first: 20): ProjectV2ItemConnection!\n  fields(first: 20): ProjectV2FieldConnection!\n}\n\ntype ProjectV2Item {\n  id: ID!\n  type: ProjectV2ItemType!\n  fieldValues(first: 10): ProjectV2ItemFieldValueConnection!\n  createdAt: DateTime!\n  updatedAt: DateTime!\n  archivedAt: DateTime\n}\n\n# Field types: SingleSelect, Text, Date, Iteration, Number, Person, PullRequest, Issue, etc.\n```\n\n**Registry Design**:\n- Centralized: Organization/user-level projects\n- Flexible: Custom fields per project\n- Items: Issues, PRs, Draft Items\n\n**Query Modes**:\n| Mode | Mechanism |\n|------|-----------|\n| By name | `title` field, search via `q` parameter |\n| By status | Single-select field (\"Status\") |\n| By lifecycle | Iteration field (sprints) |\n| By type | `item.type` (Issue/PR/Draft) |\n| By tags | Labels on linked Issues/PRs |\n| By owner | `assignees` on linked Issues/PRs |\n| By updated time | `updatedAt`, `archivedAt` |\n\n**Key Insight**: GitHub Projects V2 has no native concept of \"owner\" for the project itself — ownership is on items via assignees.\n\n---\n\n### 1.5 Backstage catalog-info.yaml\n\n**Documentation**: [Descriptor Format](https://backstage.io/docs/features/software-catalog/descriptor-format)\n\n**Metadata Schema**:\n```yaml\napiVersion: backstage.io/v1alpha1\nkind: Component\nmetadata:\n  name: artist-web\n  namespace: default\n  description: The artist portal\n  labels:\n    example.com/custom: label-value\n  annotations:\n    github.com/project-slug: example-org/artist-website\n    circleci.com/project-slug: github/example-org/artist-website\n  tags: [\"java\", \"react\"]\n  links:\n    - url: https://admin.example.com\n      title: Admin Dashboard\n      icon: dashboard\n      type: admin-dashboards\nspec:\n  type: website\n  lifecycle: production\n  owner: artist-relations-team\n  system: public-websites\n  dependsOn: [\"component:default/artist-api\"]\n```\n\n**Kinds**: `Component`, `Template`, `API`, `Group`, `User`, `Resource`, `System`, `Domain`, `Location`\n\n**Registry Design**:\n- Distributed: `catalog-info.yaml` per entity, co-located with source\n- Ingestion: `catalog-info.yaml` files registered via locations\n- Relations: `ownedBy`, `partOf`, `dependsOn`, `providesApi`, etc.\n\n**Query Modes**:\n| Mode | Mechanism |\n|------|-----------|\n| By name | `metadata.name` (unique per kind+namespace) |\n| By status | `status.items` (processing errors) |\n| By lifecycle | `spec.lifecycle` (experimental/production/deprecated) |\n| By type | `spec.type` (service/website/library) |\n| By tags | `metadata.tags` array |\n| By owner | `spec.owner` (entity reference) |\n| By updated time | `metadata.uid` (generated), external |\n| By system | `spec.system` (entity reference) |\n\n**Key Insight**: Backstage distinguishes `labels` (key-value, for classification) from `tags` (simple strings) and `annotations` (external system references).\n\n---\n\n### 1.6 Kubernetes Labels & Selectors\n\n**Documentation**: [Labels and Selectors](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-with-objects/labels/)\n\n**Metadata Schema**:\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nmetadata:\n  labels:\n    app: nginx\n    environment: production\n    tier: frontend\nspec:\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: nginx\n    matchExpressions:\n      - {key: tier, operator: In, values: [frontend, backend]}\n      - {key: environment, operator: Exists}\n```\n\n**Selector Types**:\n```go\n// Equality-based\nenv = production\ntier != frontend\n\n// Set-based\ntier in (frontend, backend)\nenvironment notin (dev, test)\napp exists\n```\n\n**Registry Design**:\n- Centralized: etcd\n- Label format: `prefix/key` (optional DNS prefix) + `/name`\n- Well-known prefixes: `app.kubernetes.io/`\n\n**Query Modes**:\n| Mode | Mechanism |\n|------|-----------|\n| By name | `metadata.name` (not a label) |\n| By status | `status` condition types |\n| By lifecycle | Custom labels (e.g., `phase: running`) |\n| By type | `kind` field |\n| By tags | Labels |\n| By owner | `metadata.ownerReferences` |\n| By updated time | `metadata.managedFields` |\n\n**Key Insight**: Kubernetes labels follow a strict format (`prefix/name`) with reserved prefixes. `matchExpressions` enables set-based queries that `matchLabels` cannot.\n\n---\n\n### 1.7 ADR (Architecture Decision Record) Index Pattern\n\n**Documentation**: [ADR GitHub org](https://adr.github.io/), [Martin Fowler's BLiki](https://martinfowler.com/bliki/ArchitectureDecisionRecord.html)\n\n**File Convention**:\n```\ndoc/\n├── adr/\n│   ├── README.md           # Index\n│   ├── 0001-use-postgresql.md\n│   ├── 0002-adopt-event-sourcing.md\n│   └── 0003-deprecate-mongodb.md   # Superseded\n```\n\n**ADR Schema** (per file):\n```markdown\n# ADR-003: MongoDB for User Profiles\n\n## Status\nDeprecated (2024-01-15)\n\n## Context\nWe needed a flexible schema for user profiles...\n\n## Decision\nWe will use MongoDB for user profile storage.\n\n## Consequences\n- Flexible schema for different profile types\n- Additional operational complexity\n\n## Superseded By\n[ADR-0020: Deprecate MongoDB](./0020-deprecate-mongodb.md)\n```\n\n**Index Schema** (README.md):\n```markdown\n| #   | Title                          | Status     | Date       |\n|-----|--------------------------------|------------|------------|\n| 0001 | Use PostgreSQL as Primary DB   | Accepted   | 2024-01-10 |\n| 0002 | Caching Strategy with Redis    | Accepted   | 2024-01-12 |\n| 0003 | MongoDB for User Profiles      | Deprecated | 2023-06-15 |\n```\n\n**Query Modes**:\n| Mode | Mechanism |\n|------|-----------|\n| By name | Filename slug + title |\n| By status | Status field (Proposed/Accepted/Deprecated/Superseded/Rejected) |\n| By number | Sequence number (0001, 0002...) |\n| By date | Decision date |\n| By topic | Full-text search in context/decision |\n\n**Key Insight**: ADRs are immutable once accepted — status changes only via supersession. This creates an auditable decision history.\n\n---\n\n### 1.8 Task/Backlog Systems\n\n**TICK.md** (from `tick.md`):\n```yaml\nschema_version: \"1.0\"\ncreated: 2026-02-05T09:00:00-05:00\nupdated: 2026-02-07T14:32:00-05:00\ndefault_workflow: [backlog, todo, in_progress, review, done]\n\n# Agent Registry\nagents:\n  - id: agent-1\n    name: \"orchestrator\"\n    role: \"coordination\"\n\n---\n\n## Tasks\n\n- id: TASK-001\n  status: done\n  priority: high\n  assigned_to: agent-1\n  created_by: human\n  tags: [\"backend\", \"api\"]\n  depends_on: []\n  history:\n    - {agent: human, action: created, timestamp: \"2026-02-05T09:00:00Z\"}\n    - {agent: agent-1, action: completed, timestamp: \"2026-02-06T14:00:00Z\"}\n```\n\n**backlog.md**:\n```yaml\nbacklog/\n├── backlog.md               # Ordered item list\n└── work/\n    └── item-slug/\n        ├── index.md         # Task breakdown\n        └── 001-task-slug.md\n```\n\n**TaskRepo** (from `taskrepo`):\n```yaml\n# tasks/task-{uuid}.md\n---\nuuid: xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx\nstatus: completed\ncreated: 2024-01-15T10:00:00Z\nmodified: 2024-01-16T14:30:00Z\npriority: H\nproject: myproject\nassignees: [\"@alice\", \"@bob\"]\ndepends: [yyyyyyyy-yyyy-yyyy-yyyy-yyyyyyyyyyyy]\n---\n## Description\nImplement the feature...\n```\n\n**Query Modes** (across systems):\n| Mode | TICK.md | backlog.md | TaskRepo | TaskBadger |\n|------|---------|------------|----------|------------|\n| By name | id field | filename | title | name |\n| By status | status enum | state files | status | status |\n| By priority | priority enum | priority field | priority | priority |\n| By assignee | assigned_to | assignees | assignees | - |\n| By tags | tags array | tags | category | tags |\n| By updated time | history | - | modified | - |\n| By due date | - | - | due | - |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Cross-Cutting Patterns\n\n### 2.1 Metadata Schema Patterns\n\n| Pattern | Systems | Example |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| **Flat key-value** | Kubernetes labels, GitHub Projects | `environment: production` |\n| **Inheritable keys** | Cargo workspace, Nx | `{key}.workspace = true` |\n| **Structured types** | Backstage, Nx targets | `spec.type`, `targets.build` |\n| **Free-form extension** | Cargo metadata, pyproject.toml `[tool.*]` | `workspace.metadata.webcontents` |\n| **Versioned schema** | Backstage (apiVersion), pyproject.toml | `backstage.io/v1alpha1` |\n\n### 2.2 Registry Discovery Patterns\n\n| Pattern | Systems | Mechanism |\n|---------|---------|-----------|\n| **Central registry** | Cargo (root Cargo.toml), Nx (nx.json) | Explicit membership list |\n| **Distributed + central** | Nx (project.json + nx.json) | Project inference |\n| **Distributed co-located** | Backstage, ADR, TaskRepo | `catalog-info.yaml` next to code |\n| **Directory convention** | ADR (`doc/adr/`), backlog.md | Fixed paths + glob |\n| **External service** | GitHub Projects, TaskBadger | API-based registry |\n\n### 2.3 Query Mode Support Matrix\n\n| System | By Name | By Status | By Type/Kind | By Tags/Labels | By Owner | By Time |\n|--------|---------|-----------|--------------|----------------|----------|---------|\n| Cargo workspaces | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ❌ (metadata) | ❌ | ❌ |\n| Nx project.json | ✅ | ⚠","metadata":{"truncated":false,"task_id":"bg_8549826c","agent":"librarian","category":"","description":"Research project registries","sessionId":"ses_241b23c79ffeRMl70ekzvJT6yI"},"title":"librarian - Research project registries","time":{"start":1777014456131,"end":1777014456165}},"id":"prt_dbe50bd2b001Sx98WwWEfggOpT","sessionID":"ses_241d9f7b3ffeMqi0Lc2w61CcA3","messageID":"msg_dbe5097c3001L4EZSncBUrWX7Y"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1777014456168,"sessionID":"ses_241d9f7b3ffeMqi0Lc2w61CcA3","part":{"id":"prt_dbe50bf670010lmyGCo2sMqXIi","reason":"tool-calls","messageID":"msg_dbe5097c3001L4EZSncBUrWX7Y","sessionID":"ses_241d9f7b3ffeMqi0Lc2w61CcA3","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":136055,"input":118562,"output":85,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":17408}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1777014466349,"sessionID":"ses_241d9f7b3ffeMqi0Lc2w61CcA3","part":{"id":"prt_dbe50e72c001pyEvFux2WY5hNL","messageID":"msg_dbe50bf6d001ZSuZ3Ac03fX9By","sessionID":"ses_241d9f7b3ffeMqi0Lc2w61CcA3","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1777014596143,"sessionID":"ses_241d9f7b3ffeMqi0Lc2w61CcA3","part":{"id":"prt_dbe50eddf001qs6OOxaybbiqvS","messageID":"msg_dbe50bf6d001ZSuZ3Ac03fX9By","sessionID":"ses_241d9f7b3ffeMqi0Lc2w61CcA3","type":"text","text":"千束，librarian 的调研也回来了。它进一步验证了：**project-manager 的项目结构最好采用“分布式项目事实源 + 中央 registry/index”的模式**，并且字段设计应该借鉴 Backstage / Kubernetes / Nx 这类“可查询目录系统”。\n\n我把之前方案再收敛成一个更明确的 **Project Structure v0.4**。\n\n---\n\n# Project Structure v0.4\n\n## 0. 总体判断\n\n我建议采用：\n\n```text\n每个项目内：\n  .agent-project/project.json 作为项目事实来源\n\nproject-manager 全局：\n  registry.json 作为项目注册表\n  index.json / 派生索引作为查询加速\n```\n\n核心模式：\n\n```text\ndistributed source of truth + central query registry\n```\n\n对应：\n\n| 系统 | 模式 |\n|---|---|\n| Backstage | 每个 repo 有 `catalog-info.yaml`，统一进 Catalog |\n| Nx | 每个项目有 `project.json`，workspace 统一发现/查询 |\n| Cargo | workspace root 管 `members`，每个 crate 也有自己的 `Cargo.toml` |\n| Kubernetes | 对象自带 metadata/labels，API server 支持 selector 查询 |\n| project-manager | 每个项目有 `.agent-project/project.json`，全局 registry 支持查询 |\n\n---\n\n# 1. 目录结构总览\n\n## 1.1 project-manager 能力自身目录\n\n也就是规则能力包：\n\n```text\nD:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\agent-system-rules\\project-manager\\\n  README.md\n  SKILL.md\n  USER_MANUAL.md\n  REGISTRATION.md\n\n  schemas/\n    project.schema.json\n    registry.schema.json\n    task.schema.json\n    next-action.schema.json\n    decision.schema.json\n    operation.schema.json\n\n  templates/\n    project.json\n    status.md\n    task.json\n    next-action.json\n    decision.md\n    runbook.md\n\n  scripts/\n    project-manager.ps1\n    register-to-mycli.ps1\n\n  src/\n    project_manager.py\n\n  examples/\n    finite_capability_project/\n    ongoing_asset_library/\n    ongoing_daily_news/\n\n  tests/\n```\n\n后续同步到：\n\n```text\nD:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\mycli\\project-manager\\\n```\n\n其中 mycli 侧可以有：\n\n```text\nmycli/project-manager/\n  cli.package.json\n  README.md\n  registry.json\n  index.json\n  scripts/\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1.2 每个被管理项目内的结构\n\n推荐：\n\n```text\n{project-root}/\n  .agent-project/\n    project.json\n    status.md\n\n    tasks/\n      task-0001.json\n      task-0002.json\n\n    next-actions/\n      next-0001.json\n      next-0002.json\n\n    decisions/\n      ADR-0001-title.md\n      index.json\n\n    context/\n      index.json\n      pinned-files.md\n      architecture.md\n      glossary.md\n\n    operations/\n      runbook.md\n      schedule.json\n      last-run.json\n      history.jsonl\n\n    artifacts/\n      index.json\n\n    runs/\n      agent-runs.json\n      workflow-runs.json\n\n    handoffs/\n      2026-04-24.md\n\n    reviews/\n      review-0001.md\n\n    .generated/\n      summary.json\n      search-doc.json\n      last-indexed.json\n```\n\n## 1.3 MVP 结构\n\n第一版可以简化成：\n\n```text\n.agent-project/\n  project.json\n  status.md\n  tasks/\n  next-actions/\n  decisions/\n  context/\n    index.json\n  operations/\n    runbook.md\n  runs/\n  handoffs/\n  .generated/\n```\n\n如果更极简：\n\n```text\n.agent-project/\n  project.json\n  status.md\n  tasks/\n  next-actions/\n```\n\n但我建议 `operations/` 一开始就保留，因为你明确提到持续运行型项目。\n\n---\n\n# 2. `project.json` 顶层结构\n\n我建议借鉴 Backstage 的 envelope 模型：\n\n```json\n{\n  \"apiVersion\": \"agent-project/v1\",\n  \"kind\": \"Project\",\n  \"metadata\": {},\n  \"spec\": {},\n  \"status\": {},\n  \"current\": {},\n  \"operations\": {},\n  \"relations\": {},\n  \"timestamps\": {}\n}\n```\n\n## 为什么这样分？\n\n| 区块 | 职责 | 更新频率 |\n|---|---|---|\n| `apiVersion` | schema 版本 | 很少 |\n| `kind` | 对象类型，未来可扩展 ProjectGroup | 很少 |\n| `metadata` | 名称、描述、标签、owner、查询元数据 | 中低 |\n| `spec` | 项目本质定义，目标、范围、模式 | 中低 |\n| `status` | 当前状态 | 高频 |\n| `current` | 当前推进项 | 高频 |\n| `operations` | 持续运行信息 | 高频/自动 |\n| `relations` | 和项目、workflow、skill、repo 的关系 | 中 |\n| `timestamps` | 时间戳 | 高频 |\n\n这个结构的好处是：\n\n- 机器好解析；\n- 人也容易理解；\n- 查询字段可以从 `metadata/spec/status/current/operations` 中压平到 registry；\n- 后续 schema 迁移容易。\n\n---\n\n# 3. `metadata` 设计\n\n`metadata` 主要服务于 **发现、展示、查询、归类**。\n\n```json\n\"metadata\": {\n  \"id\": \"daily-hot-news\",\n  \"name\": \"每日新闻热点收集\",\n  \"aliases\": [\"热点收集\", \"daily-news\"],\n  \"description\": \"每天自动收集和整理热点新闻主题。\",\n  \"root\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\projects\\\\daily-hot-news\",\n  \"owner\": \"千束\",\n  \"domain\": \"content-ops\",\n  \"tags\": [\"daily\", \"news\", \"hot-topics\", \"automation\"],\n  \"labels\": {\n    \"agent.project/type\": \"research\",\n    \"agent.project/mode\": \"ongoing\",\n    \"agent.project/domain\": \"content-ops\",\n    \"agent.project/managed-by\": \"project-manager\"\n  },\n  \"annotations\": {\n    \"notes\": \"持续运行型内容运营项目\"\n  },\n  \"links\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"Project README\",\n      \"url\": \"README.md\",\n      \"type\": \"docs\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## 3.1 `id`\n\n必须稳定。\n\n建议规则：\n\n```text\n小写 kebab-case\n不要用中文作为 id\n不要频繁改\n```\n\n示例：\n\n```text\nproject-manager\ndaily-hot-news\nasset-library\nagent-workflow\n```\n\n## 3.2 `name`\n\n人类可读，可以中文：\n\n```json\n\"name\": \"每日新闻热点收集\"\n```\n\n## 3.3 `aliases`\n\n用于名称查询。\n\n比如用户说：\n\n```text\n热点项目\n每日新闻\ndaily-news\n```\n\n都可以匹配到同一项目。\n\n## 3.4 `tags` vs `labels` vs `annotations`\n\n这三者要区分清楚。\n\n| 字段 | 类型 | 用途 |\n|---|---|---|\n| `tags` | string[] | 人类友好的松散标签 |\n| `labels` | key/value | 机器查询、selector、分类 |\n| `annotations` | key/value | 外部系统引用、备注、非筛选主字段 |\n\n借鉴 Kubernetes / Backstage：\n\n```json\n\"tags\": [\"automation\", \"news\"]\n```\n\n用于简单查询：\n\n```powershell\nquery --tag automation\n```\n\n```json\n\"labels\": {\n  \"agent.project/mode\": \"ongoing\"\n}\n```\n\n用于结构化查询：\n\n```powershell\nquery --selector \"agent.project/mode=ongoing\"\n```\n\n```json\n\"annotations\": {\n  \"github.com/project-slug\": \"owner/repo\"\n}\n```\n\n用于外部系统引用，不一定参与核心筛选。\n\n---\n\n# 4. `spec` 设计\n\n`spec` 代表项目的相对稳定定义。\n\n```json\n\"spec\": {\n  \"project_type\": \"research\",\n  \"project_mode\": \"ongoing\",\n  \"priority\": \"high\",\n  \"visibility\": \"private\",\n  \"stale_after_days\": 14,\n  \"source\": {\n    \"kind\": \"local\",\n    \"path\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\projects\\\\daily-hot-news\"\n  },\n  \"goals\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"goal-0001\",\n      \"title\": \"持续收集每日热点并生成摘要\",\n      \"status\": \"active\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"scope\": {\n    \"in\": [\n      \"热点采集\",\n      \"摘要生成\",\n      \"每日归档\"\n    ],\n    \"out\": [\n      \"自动发布到外部平台\"\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## 4.1 `project_type`\n\n建议：\n\n```text\ncapability\nworkflow\ncoding\nresearch\ndocumentation\nops\nexperiment\nexternal_repo\nmeta\n```\n\n## 4.2 `project_mode`\n\n```text\nfinite\nongoing\n```\n\n这是最重要字段之一。\n\n- `finite`：有限交付型；\n- `ongoing`：持续运行/持续维护型。\n\n## 4.3 `priority`\n\n```text\nlow\nmedium\nhigh\ncritical\n```\n\n## 4.4 `source.kind`\n\n```text\nlocal\ngit\nexternal\nvirtual\n```\n\n---\n\n# 5. `status` 设计\n\n沿用我们刚定的 v0.3 状态模型。\n\n```json\n\"status\": {\n  \"registration\": \"indexed\",\n  \"lifecycle\": \"active\",\n  \"phase\": \"operations\",\n  \"activity\": \"stable\",\n  \"health\": \"green\",\n  \"delivery\": \"published\",\n  \"attention\": [],\n  \"summary\": \"每日热点收集稳定运行。\",\n  \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:10:00+08:00\",\n  \"updated_by\": \"scheduler\"\n}\n```\n\n## 5.1 枚举\n\n```text\nregistration:\n  discovered | registered | indexed | stale | missing | retired\n\nlifecycle:\n  proposed | planned | active | paused | completed | retired | archived\n\nphase:\n  intake | requirements | feasibility | architecture | planning |\n  construction | validation | launch | operations | maintenance |\n  retirement | closure\n\nactivity:\n  queued | in_progress | scheduled | stable | running |\n  waiting | blocked | degraded | paused | needs_attention\n\nhealth:\n  green | yellow | red | gray\n\ndelivery:\n  none | concept | draft | prototype | usable |\n  delivered | verified | published | deprecated\n```\n\n## 5.2 attention\n\n```text\nneeds_user_decision\nneeds_user_input\nneeds_scope_confirmation\nneeds_review\nneeds_validation\nneeds_unblock\nneeds_cleanup\nneeds_handoff\nneeds_maintenance\nneeds_operation_check\nneeds_schedule_setup\nneeds_runbook\nneeds_retirement_decision\n```\n\n---\n\n# 6. `current` 设计\n\n`current` 是项目首页最有用的部分，回答：\n\n```text\n现在正在推进什么？\n下一步是什么？\n卡在哪里？\n```\n\n```json\n\"current\": {\n  \"goal_id\": \"goal-0001\",\n  \"milestone_id\": null,\n  \"task_id\": \"task-0001\",\n  \"next_action_id\": \"next-0001\",\n  \"summary\": \"确认项目结构 v0.4，并准备 project.json schema。\",\n  \"owner\": \"assistant\",\n  \"since\": \"2026-04-24T09:00:00+08:00\"\n}\n```\n\n原则：\n\n1. 一个项目最多一个 `current.task_id`。\n2. 可以有多个 next-actions，但 `current.next_action_id` 指向当前最重要的。\n3. 如果没有当前推进项，`activity` 应该是 `stable` / `queued` / `waiting`，而不是假装 `in_progress`。\n4. `current` 只存引用和摘要，不存完整任务正文。\n\n---\n\n# 7. `operations` 设计\n\n对 `project_mode = ongoing` 的项目非常重要。\n\n```json\n\"operations\": {\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"cadence\": \"daily\",\n  \"trigger\": \"schedule\",\n  \"schedule_expr\": \"0 8 * * *\",\n  \"last_run_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:00:00+08:00\",\n  \"last_run_status\": \"success\",\n  \"last_success_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:00:00+08:00\",\n  \"next_run_at\": \"2026-04-25T08:00:00+08:00\",\n  \"consecutive_failures\": 0,\n  \"run_count_7d\": 7,\n  \"success_count_7d\": 7,\n  \"output_summary\": \"Collected 32 hot topics and generated daily digest.\",\n  \"runbook\": \".agent-project/operations/runbook.md\"\n}\n```\n\n## 7.1 `cadence`\n\n```text\non_demand\nhourly\ndaily\nweekly\nmonthly\nevent_driven\ndaemon\nmanual\n```\n\n## 7.2 `trigger`\n\n```text\nmanual\nschedule\nevent\nwatcher\ndaemon\nagent\nworkflow\n```\n\n## 7.3 `last_run_status`\n\n```text\nsuccess\npartial\nfailed\nskipped\nunknown\n```\n\n对于 `finite` 项目：\n\n```json\n\"operations\": null\n```\n\n或者：\n\n```json\n\"operations\": {\n  \"enabled\": false\n}\n```\n\n我更建议第一版用：\n\n```json\n\"operations\": null\n```\n\n简单。\n\n---\n\n# 8. `relations` 设计\n\n项目结构要支持跨项目查询，所以 relations 必须有。\n\n```json\n\"relations\": {\n  \"depends_on_projects\": [],\n  \"related_projects\": [],\n  \"parent_project\": null,\n  \"child_projects\": [],\n  \"workflows\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"daily_news_flow\",\n      \"path\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\projects\\\\daily-hot-news\\\\workflow.json\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"skills\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"news-collector\",\n      \"path\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\capability-library\\\\skill-library\\\\news-collector\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"repos\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"git\",\n      \"path\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\projects\\\\daily-hot-news\",\n      \"remote\": null\n    }\n  ],\n  \"artifacts\": []\n}\n```\n\n可支持：\n\n```powershell\nquery --depends-on asset-library\nquery --related daily-hot-news\nquery --workflow daily_news_flow\nquery --skill news-collector\n```\n\n---\n\n# 9. `timestamps` 设计\n\n```json\n\"timestamps\": {\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-04-24T00:00:00+08:00\",\n  \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:10:00+08:00\",\n  \"last_activity_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:10:00+08:00\",\n  \"last_indexed_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:11:00+08:00\"\n}\n```\n\n查询陈旧项目要靠它。\n\n---\n\n# 10. 完整 `project.json` 示例\n\n```json\n{\n  \"apiVersion\": \"agent-project/v1\",\n  \"kind\": \"Project\",\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"id\": \"daily-hot-news\",\n    \"name\": \"每日新闻热点收集\",\n    \"aliases\": [\"热点收集\", \"daily-news\"],\n    \"description\": \"每天自动收集和整理热点新闻主题。\",\n    \"root\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\projects\\\\daily-hot-news\",\n    \"owner\": \"千束\",\n    \"domain\": \"content-ops\",\n    \"tags\": [\"daily\", \"news\", \"hot-topics\", \"automation\"],\n    \"labels\": {\n      \"agent.project/type\": \"research\",\n      \"agent.project/mode\": \"ongoing\",\n      \"agent.project/domain\": \"content-ops\",\n      \"agent.project/managed-by\": \"project-manager\"\n    },\n    \"annotations\": {\n      \"notes\": \"持续运行型内容运营项目\"\n    },\n    \"links\": [\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Project README\",\n        \"url\": \"README.md\",\n        \"type\": \"docs\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"spec\": {\n    \"project_type\": \"research\",\n    \"project_mode\": \"ongoing\",\n    \"priority\": \"high\",\n    \"visibility\": \"private\",\n    \"stale_after_days\": 14,\n    \"source\": {\n      \"kind\": \"local\",\n      \"path\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\projects\\\\daily-hot-news\"\n    },\n    \"goals\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"goal-0001\",\n        \"title\": \"持续收集每日热点并生成摘要\",\n        \"status\": \"active\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"scope\": {\n      \"in\": [\"热点采集\", \"摘要生成\", \"每日归档\"],\n      \"out\": [\"自动发布到外部平台\"]\n    }\n  },\n  \"status\": {\n    \"registration\": \"indexed\",\n    \"lifecycle\": \"active\",\n    \"phase\": \"operations\",\n    \"activity\": \"stable\",\n    \"health\": \"green\",\n    \"delivery\": \"published\",\n    \"attention\": [],\n    \"summary\": \"每日热点收集稳定运行。\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:10:00+08:00\",\n    \"updated_by\": \"scheduler\"\n  },\n  \"current\": {\n    \"goal_id\": \"goal-0001\",\n    \"milestone_id\": null,\n    \"task_id\": null,\n    \"next_action_id\": \"next-ops-check\",\n    \"summary\": \"等待下一次定时运行。\",\n    \"owner\": \"scheduler\",\n    \"since\": \"2026-04-24T08:10:00+08:00\"\n  },\n  \"operations\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"cadence\": \"daily\",\n    \"trigger\": \"schedule\",\n    \"schedule_expr\": \"0 8 * * *\",\n    \"last_run_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:00:00+08:00\",\n    \"last_run_status\": \"success\",\n    \"last_success_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:00:00+08:00\",\n    \"next_run_at\": \"2026-04-25T08:00:00+08:00\",\n    \"consecutive_failures\": 0,\n    \"run_count_7d\": 7,\n    \"success_count_7d\": 7,\n    \"output_summary\": \"Collected 32 hot topics and generated daily digest.\",\n    \"runbook\": \".agent-project/operations/runbook.md\"\n  },\n  \"relations\": {\n    \"depends_on_projects\": [],\n    \"related_projects\": [],\n    \"parent_project\": null,\n    \"child_projects\": [],\n    \"workflows\": [],\n    \"skills\": [],\n    \"repos\": [],\n    \"artifacts\": []\n  },\n  \"timestamps\": {\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-04-24T00:00:00+08:00\",\n    \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:10:00+08:00\",\n    \"last_activity_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:10:00+08:00\",\n    \"last_indexed_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:11:00+08:00\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n# 11. 全局 registry 结构\n\n全局 registry 是查询入口。\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schema_version\": \"agent-project-registry/v1\",\n  \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:11:00+08:00\",\n  \"source_roots\": [\n    \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\projects\",\n    \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\capability-library\"\n  ],\n  \"projects\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"daily-hot-news\",\n      \"name\": \"每日新闻热点收集\",\n      \"aliases\": [\"热点收集\", \"daily-news\"],\n      \"description\": \"每天自动收集和整理热点新闻主题。\",\n      \"root\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\projects\\\\daily-hot-news\",\n      \"project_file\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\projects\\\\daily-hot-news\\\\.agent-project\\\\project.json\",\n      \"status_file\": \"D:\\\\agent_workspace\\\\projects\\\\daily-hot-news\\\\.agent-project\\\\status.md\",\n\n      \"project_type\": \"research\",\n      \"project_mode\": \"ongoing\",\n      \"owner\": \"千束\",\n      \"domain\": \"content-ops\",\n      \"priority\": \"high\",\n      \"tags\": [\"daily\", \"news\", \"hot-topics\", \"automation\"],\n      \"labels\": {\n        \"agent.project/type\": \"research\",\n        \"agent.project/mode\": \"ongoing\"\n      },\n\n      \"registration\": \"indexed\",\n      \"lifecycle\": \"active\",\n      \"phase\": \"operations\",\n      \"activity\": \"stable\",\n      \"health\": \"green\",\n      \"delivery\": \"published\",\n      \"attention\": [],\n\n      \"current_goal_id\": \"goal-0001\",\n      \"current_task_id\": null,\n      \"current_next_action_id\": \"next-ops-check\",\n      \"summary\": \"每日热点收集稳定运行。\",\n\n      \"operations_enabled\": true,\n      \"operations_cadence\": \"daily\",\n      \"operations_trigger\": \"schedule\",\n      \"last_run_status\": \"success\",\n      \"next_run_at\": \"2026-04-25T08:00:00+08:00\",\n      \"consecutive_failures\": 0,\n\n      \"last_activity_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:10:00+08:00\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:10:00+08:00\",\n      \"last_indexed_at\": \"2026-04-24T08:11:00+08:00\",\n      \"is_missing\": false,\n      \"is_stale\": false\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## 核心原则\n\n```text\nproject.json = truth\nregistry.json = query cache\n```\n\nregistry 可以删掉重建，不应该人工维护为主。\n\n---\n\n# 12. 查询模式设计\n\n## 12.1 基础查询\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager query\nmycli project-manager query --id daily-hot-news\nmycli project-manager query --name news\nmycli project-manager query --name 热点\n```\n\n`--name` 应匹配：\n\n```text\nid\nname\naliases\ndescription\n```\n\n也可以分开：\n\n```powershell\n--id\n--name\n--alias\n--text\n```\n\n但第一版 `--name` 做模糊匹配即可。\n\n---\n\n## 12.2 类型查询\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager query --type research\nmycli project-manager query --mode ongoing\nmycli project-manager query --owner 千束\nmycli project-manager query --domain content-ops\nmycli project-manager query --priority high\nmycli project-manager query --tag automation\n```\n\n---\n\n## 12.3 状态查询\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager query --registration indexed\nmycli project-manager query --lifecycle active\nmycli project-manager query --phase operations\nmycli project-manager query --activity stable\nmycli project-manager query --health yellow\nmycli project-manager query --delivery published\nmycli project-manager query --attention needs_maintenance\n```\n\n组合查询默认 AND：\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager query --mode ongoing --health yellow\nmycli project-manager query --lifecycle active --attention needs_user_decision\nmycli project-manager query --phase maintenance --activity blocked\n```\n\n---\n\n## 12.4 持续运行查询\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager query --operations-enabled\nmycli project-manager query --cadence daily\nmycli project-manager query --last-run-status failed\nmycli project-manager query --consecutive-failures 3\nmycli project-manager query --next-run-before 2026-04-25T00:00:00+08:00\n```\n\n第一版可以先支持：\n\n```powershell\n--mode ongoing\n--last-run-status failed\n--health red\n--attention needs_operation_check\n```\n\n不急着做复杂时间比较。\n\n---\n\n## 12.5 时间/陈旧查询\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager query --stale\nmycli project-manager query --updated-before 2026-04-01\nmycli project-manager query --inactive-days 14\n```\n\n陈旧判断：\n\n```text\nis_stale = now - status.updated_at > spec.stale_after_days\n```\n\n持续项目可以额外判断：\n\n```text\nnow > operations.next_run_at + tolerance\nlast_run_status failed\nconsecutive_failures > 0\n```\n\n---\n\n## 12.6 selector 查询\n\n未来支持 Kubernetes 风格：\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager query --selector \"agent.project/mode=ongoing,agent.project/domain=content-ops\"\n```\n\n再高级一点：\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager query --selector \"agent.project/type in (research,documentation),agent.project/mode=ongoing\"\n```\n\n但 MVP 不要先做复杂 parser，先保留 `labels` 结构即可。\n\n---\n\n# 13. 查询输出\n\n## 13.1 默认 table\n\n```text\nid              name              type      mode     lifecycle  phase       activity  health  delivery   updated\ndaily-hot-news  每日热点新闻收集  research  ongoing  active     operations  stable    green   published  2026-04-24\nproject-manager Project Manager   capability finite   planned    requirements waiting  green   concept    2026-04-24\n```\n\n## 13.2 JSON\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager query --json\n```\n\n返回 registry entries。\n\n## 13.3 详情\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager get daily-hot-news\n```\n\n读完整：\n\n```text\n.agent-project/project.json\n```\n\n## 13.4 状态页\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager status daily-hot-news\n```\n\n读：\n\n```text\n.agent-project/status.md\n```\n\n或根据 `project.json` 生成摘要。\n\n---\n\n# 14. `status.md`\n\n`status.md` 是给人/agent 快速看的。\n\n```md\n# Project Status: 每日新闻热点收集\n\n## Summary\n\n每日热点收集稳定运行。\n\n## Current State\n\n- Type: research\n- Mode: ongoing\n- Lifecycle: active\n- Phase: operations\n- Activity: stable\n- Health: green\n- Delivery: published\n- Attention: none\n\n## Current Focus\n\n等待下一次定时运行。\n\n## Operations\n\n- Cadence: daily\n- Last Run: 2026-04-24 08:00\n- Last Run Status: success\n- Next Run: 2026-04-25 08:00\n- Consecutive Failures: 0\n\n## Next Actions\n\n- next-ops-check: Monitor next scheduled run.\n\n## Risks / Blockers\n\nNone.\n\n## Recent Updates\n\n- 2026-04-24: Collected 32 hot topics and generated daily digest.\n```\n\n原则：\n\n```text\nproject.json 是结构化事实来源\nstatus.md 是快速阅读摘要\n```\n\n---\n\n# 15. task / next-action / decision 结构\n\n## 15.1 task\n\n建议一个任务一个文件：\n\n```text\n.agent-project/tasks/task-0001.json\n```\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"task-0001\",\n  \"title\": \"设计 project-manager 项目结构\",\n  \"type\": \"design\",\n  \"status\": \"in_progress\",\n  \"priority\": \"high\",\n  \"phase\": \"architecture\",\n  \"owner\": \"assistant\",\n  \"depends_on\": [],\n  \"blocks\": [],\n  \"tags\": [\"schema\", \"registry\", \"query\"],\n  \"acceptance_criteria\": [\n    \"支持项目注册\",\n    \"支持按状态查询\",\n    \"支持按生命周期查询\",\n    \"支持持续项目结构\"\n  ],\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-04-24T00:00:00+08:00\",\n  \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-24T00:00:00+08:00\"\n}\n```\n\n## 15.2 next-action\n\n```text\n.agent-project/next-actions/next-0001.json\n```\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"next-0001\",\n  \"title\": \"确认项目结构 v0.4\",\n  \"type\": \"decide\",\n  \"status\": \"open\",\n  \"priority\": \"high\",\n  \"owner\": \"千束\",\n  \"blocks\": [\"task-0002\"],\n  \"reason\": \"项目结构决定 registry、query、schema 的基础。\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-04-24T00:00:00+08:00\"\n}\n```\n\n## 15.3 decision\n\n```text\n.agent-project/decisions/ADR-0001-project-structure.md\n```\n\n```md\n# ADR-0001: Use distributed project.json plus central registry\n\n## Status\n\nProposed\n\n## Context\n\nProjects need to support query by status, lifecycle, name, type, tags, owner, and ongoing operation state.\n\n## Decision\n\nEach project owns `.agent-project/project.json` as the source of truth.\nProject Manager maintains a generated global `registry.json` for query.\n\n## Consequences\n\n- Project metadata stays near the project.\n- Registry can be rebuilt.\n- Query is fast and centralized.\n```\n\n---\n\n# 16. 注册流程\n\n## 16.1 init\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager init <project-root> --id <id> --name <name> --type <type> --mode finite|ongoing\n```\n\n生成 `.agent-project/`。\n\n## 16.2 register\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager register <project-root>\n```\n\n将项目写入 registry。\n\n## 16.3 scan\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager scan D:\\agent_workspace\\projects\n```\n\n扫描：\n\n```text\n**/.agent-project/project.json\n```\n\n## 16.4 refresh\n\n```powershell\nmycli project-manager refresh\n```\n\n重建全局 registry。\n\n---\n\n# 17. 旧 project-skill-manager 兼容\n\n旧格式：\n\n```yaml\n---\nname: 项目名称\ndescription: 一句话描述项目\nstatus: todo/done/sustained/skill_dependent\n---\n```\n\n映射：\n\n| 旧状态 | 新结构 |\n|---|---|\n| `todo` | `project_mode=finite`, `lifecycle=active/planned`, `phase=construction`, `activity=in_progress` |\n| `done` | `project_mode=finite`, `lifecycle=completed`, `phase=closure`, `activity=stable` |\n| `sustained` | `project_mode=ongoing`, `lifecycle=active`, `phase=operations`, `activity=stable` |\n| `skill_dependent` | 不作为主状态，转成 `labels/protection` |\n\n例如：\n\n```json\n\"labels\": {\n  \"agent.project/protection\": \"skill-dependent\"\n}\n```\n\n或：\n\n```json\n\"protection\": [\"skill_dependent\", \"do_not_delete\"]\n```\n\n---\n\n# 18. 最终推荐查询字段\n\nregistry 中建议压平这些字段：\n\n```text\nid\nname\naliases\ndescription\nroot\nproject_file\nstatus_file\n\nproject_type\nproject_mode\nowner\ndomain\npriority\ntags\nlabels\n\nregistration\nlifecycle\nphase\nactivity\nhealth\ndelivery\nattention\n\ncurrent_goal_id\ncurrent_task_id\ncurrent_next_action_id\nsummary\n\noperations_enabled\noperations_cadence\noperations_trigger\nlast_run_status\nnext_run_at\nconsecutive_failures\n\nlast_activity_at\nupdated_at\nlast_indexed_at\nis_missing\nis_stale\n```\n\n这样绝大多数查询都可以只查 registry。\n\n---\n\n# 19. 我建议 v0.4 拍板内容\n\n我建议锁定以下结构作为 project-manager v0.1 的基础：\n\n```text\n项目内：\n  .agent-project/project.json\n  .agent-project/status.md\n  .agent-project/tasks/\n  .agent-project/next-actions/\n  .agent-project/decisions/\n  .agent-project/context/\n  .agent-project/operations/\n  .agent-project/runs/\n  .agent-project/handoffs/\n\n全局：\n  project-manager/registry.json\n```\n\n`project.json` 顶层：\n\n```json\n{\n  \"apiVersion\": \"agent-project/v1\",\n  \"kind\": \"Project\",\n  \"metadata\": {},\n  \"spec\": {},\n  \"status\": {},\n  \"current\": {},\n  \"operations\": {},\n  \"relations\": {},\n  \"timestamps\": {}\n}\n```\n\n查询优先支持：\n\n```text\nid/name\ntype/mode\nowner/domain/tag\nlifecycle/phase/activity/health/delivery/attention\nstale/missing\nlast-run-status for ongoing\n```\n\n命令优先支持：\n\n```powershell\ninit\nregister\nscan\nrefresh\nlist\nquery\nget\nstatus\n```\n\n这套结构能覆盖：\n\n- 普通一次性项目；\n- 持续运行项目；\n- 素材库这种持续积累项目；\n- 每日新闻热点这种定时运行项目；\n- capability-library 能力建设项目；\n- 后续维护；\n- 多条件项目查询。","time":{"start":1777014468063,"end":1777014596141}}}
